      "type": "TextBlock",
      "text": "Lesson 2: Advantages of Using Cards",
      "size": "medium",
      "weight": "bolder"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextBlock",
      "text": "Bot are supposed to make work easier. In reality, text-only chat bots can be cumbersome and tedious to work with, especially when interactions get more complex. Users may need to remember complicated commands or respond to a series of questions in order to complete a task.",
      "wrap": true
    },
    {
      "type": "TextBlock",
      "text": "Compare this:",
      "weight": "Bolder"
    },
    {
      "type": "Image",
      "altText": "text bot",
      "url": "https://cardschool.webexbots.cloud/images/jira-text-bot.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextBlock",
      "text": "with this:",
      "weight": "Bolder"
    },
    {
      "type": "Image",
      "altText": "buttons and cards",
      "url": "https://cardschool.webexbots.cloud/images/jira-card-bot.jpg"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextBlock",
      "text": "Cards are essentially GUIs, which are much more intuitive and easier for users to follow. As you can see in the example above, the card uses a simple form to collect information instead of a more complex text-based interaction.",
      "wrap": true
    },
    {
      "type": "TextBlock",
      "text": "If you have previously built Webex bots or integrations, consider how the user experience of those apps can be optimized by using Buttons and Cards.",
      "wrap": true
    },
    {
      "type": "Input.ChoiceSet",
      "id": "myCardIndex",
      "value": "2",
      "isMultiSelect": false,
      "isVisible": false,
      "choices": [
